headline: Why Centene (CNC) Shares Are Sliding Today
summary: Shares of health coverage company Centene (NYSE:CNC) fell 2.9% in the afternoon session after the company highlighted a significant challenge for its Marketplace business during a recent investor conference.

headline: Centene stock uncertainty as ACA subsidy expiration looms: What investors need to know about rising medical costs and 2026 Marketplace risk
summary: Centene’s recent stock drop is closely linked to a combination of higher-than-expected medical costs amid challenging trends in the Affordable Care Act market and anticipation of the scheduled end to enhanced subsidies.

headline: Stock Index Futures Muted After Record Rally, U.S. Confidence Data on Tap
summary: September S&P 500 E-Mini futures (ESU25) are down -0.11%, and September Nasdaq 100 E-Mini futures (NQU25) are down -0.04% this morning, taking a breather as investors assess how much further the record rally fueled by expectations of Federal Reserve rate cuts can continue.
